(5311, 'Pre-Council Exam 7', 'Pre-Council Exam 7 (uploaded past-paper set)', 'A client is brought to the emergency room complaining of pressure in her chest. Her blood pressure is 150/90, pulse 88, respirations 20. The nurse administers nitro-glycerine 0.4 mg sublingually as ordered. After five minutes her blood pressure is 100/60, pulse 96, respirations 20. Which of the following should the critical care nurse do next?', '["Notify the physician that the client has become hypotensive, and obtain an order to administer IV fluids.", "Place the client in semi-Fowler\u2019s position, and administer O2 at 4 L.", "Administer a second dose of nitro-glycerine.", "Document the results, and continue to monitor the client."]'::jsonb, 3, NULL, 'Pre-Council', '🎓', true),
